Defendant in custody.
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 08-19-15.   
On Count 1 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of seven (7) years.  Three (3) years initial confinement, followed by four (4) years extended supervision.  
On Count 3 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years, concurrent with Count 1.  Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Pay costs of action;
2) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
5) Have no contact with P.A.H. or her family without agent's approval;
6) Comply with sex offender registry;
7) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
Defendant is given credit for 316 days already served.  
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.   
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
Minutes.

Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years on count 1 and for four (4) years on count 3.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
5) No contact with the victim, P.A.H., or her family without agent's approval;
6) Comply with Sex Offender registry;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) Spend six (6) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, commencing on 08-12-14 at 8:00 a.m.
Defendant is instructed to take care of his photos and prints at the Sheriff's Department.
